id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.378312362Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.314653521Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","title":"A.6: Detail modal regression test suite","description":"WHAT: Comprehensive test coverage for the enhanced detail modal: (1) Enter opens modal with correct conversation data, (2) markdown rendering produces expected output for GFM test cases, (3) tool call collapse/expand state management works correctly, (4) message-level navigation jumps to correct positions, (5) find-in-conversation highlights and navigates correctly, (6) session metadata header displays accurate data, (7) performance: modal open under 200ms, markdown render under 5ms per message. WHY: The detail modal is the most complex interactive component — regressions here are high-impact. The existing tests cover basic modal open/close but not the enhanced features. HOW: Unit tests in app.rs for state management (collapse, navigation, find), snapshot tests for rendering output, performance benchmarks. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (test module). ACCEPTANCE: All new features have test coverage, no existing tests broken, performance budgets met.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T10:00:19.506785895Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:03.794268188Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.385788200Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.457582908Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.6","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.530674601Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","title":"Feature B: Analytics Data Visualization with Full ftui Chart Suite","description":"We collect massive analytics data (18+ raw metrics, 10+ derived metrics, dual-track rollups at hourly/daily/weekly/monthly granularity) but the 8 existing analytics views (Dashboard, Explorer, Heatmap, Breakdowns, Tools, Cost, Plans, Coverage) underutilize ftui chart capabilities. The ftui-extras crate provides BarChart, LineChart, Sparkline, Canvas (with Painter API for custom rendering), and visual-fx — many of these are imported but not fully exploited. This feature enhances the analytics views to use the full ftui visualization toolkit: interactive drill-down from charts to filtered search results, canvas-rendered custom visualizations, richer chart interactivity, and hourly granularity surfacing. Key files: src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (2518 lines, renders all 8 views), src/analytics/query.rs (timeseries/breakdown/tool queries), src/analytics/types.rs (UsageBucket with all metrics).","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:08.994704526Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.1","title":"B.1: Audit ftui chart/canvas/visual-fx capabilities vs current usage and identify gaps","description":"WHAT: Systematically catalog every widget, chart type, canvas primitive, and visual effect available from ftui and ftui-extras, then compare against what cass currently uses. Produce a gap analysis showing which features are available but unused. WHY: We pay the compile cost for all ftui-extras features (markdown, syntax, charts, canvas, visual-fx, forms, validation, help) but only use a fraction. The ftui demo showcase demonstrates capabilities we should be leveraging. Without this audit we are guessing at what is possible. HOW: (1) Read ftui-extras source/docs at the pinned git rev (f0ad8a6d9b016ce6a000dc5e1461e1411aee1441), (2) list all public types/widgets/functions, (3) grep cass source for current usage, (4) categorize gaps as high/medium/low value, (5) write findings to docs/ftui_feature_audit.md. Focus on: chart interactivity (hover, selection, drill-down), canvas drawing primitives (lines, circles, text, fill), visual-fx (what animations/effects are available), form widgets (what input types exist). KEY FILES: Cargo.toml (ftui-extras features), Cargo.lock (pinned rev), src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (current chart usage), src/ui/ftui_adapter.rs (current imports). ACCEPTANCE: Audit document listing all available features, current usage status, and prioritized gap recommendations.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:55.681621997Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T08:50:32.898508388Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T08:50:32.898484764Z","close_reason":"Completed: authored docs/ftui_feature_audit.md with capability inventory and prioritized gap analysis","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:55.681621997Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.2","title":"B.2: Implement interactive chart drill-down from analytics to filtered search","description":"WHAT: When viewing analytics charts (bar charts, heatmap cells, line chart points), allow the user to press Enter on a selected data element to drill down into filtered search results for that dimension. For example: clicking a bar in the top-agents chart filters search to that agent; clicking a heatmap cell filters to that date; clicking a line chart point shows sessions from that time period. WHY: Analytics without drill-down is a dead end. Users see interesting patterns (spike in token usage, unexpected agent activity) but cannot investigate further without manually typing filters. Drill-down creates the analytics-to-search flow that makes the TUI genuinely useful for investigation. HOW: (1) Add selection state to chart views (selected_bar_idx, selected_cell, etc.), (2) handle Enter in analytics views to construct a filter (agent, workspace, date range), (3) dispatch CassMsg that applies the filter and switches to search view, (4) show breadcrumb indicating drill-down origin. Heatmap cells map to date ranges, bar chart bars map to dimension values, line chart points map to time buckets. KEY FILES: src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (chart rendering), src/ui/app.rs (analytics key handling at lines 8114-8232, filter state). ACCEPTANCE: Enter on any chart element drills down to appropriately filtered search results, with breadcrumb showing drill-down context.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:56.062653217Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:17:49.904201903Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T09:17:49.904155396Z","close_reason":"Completed: analytics drilldown now applies workspace/source dimension filters; added context + override tests; validated via check/clippy/fmt and analytics_drilldown test suite.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies