-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.3","title":"B.3: Add hourly-granularity timeline view to analytics Explorer","description":"WHAT: The analytics Explorer currently defaults to daily/weekly/monthly time buckets. Add hourly granularity option, rendering a dense timeline that shows intraday patterns (when are agents most active, token usage spikes, cost patterns within a day). WHY: The hourly rollup data exists in usage_hourly table but is not surfaced in the TUI. Hourly patterns reveal important information: overnight agent runs, peak usage hours, cost optimization opportunities. This was listed as a gap in the analytics audit — stored but not surfaced. HOW: (1) Add GroupBy::Hour option to the Explorer metric selector, (2) query usage_hourly table when hourly granularity selected, (3) render with LineChart using denser x-axis (24 ticks per day vs 1), (4) add date range selector since hourly data for long periods is too dense — default to last 7 days when hourly selected. KEY FILES: src/ui/analytics_charts.rs (render_explorer), src/analytics/query.rs (query_tokens_timeseries with GroupBy), src/analytics/types.rs (GroupBy enum, already has Hour variant). ACCEPTANCE: Explorer view shows hourly granularity option, renders clean timeline for last 7 days, auto-switches to daily for longer ranges.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:56.725181366Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T09:20:42.769742024Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:58:56.725181366Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:29.673513670Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
