 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","title":"C.3: Add inline mini-analytics to search result list items","description":"WHAT: Enrich each search result item in the results list with compact analytics: (1) small token count badge (e.g. '2.1K tok'), (2) cost badge if above threshold (e.g. '$0.42'), (3) message count ('47 msgs'), (4) tiny agent-colored dot indicator. These render in the right margin of each result item, taking advantage of the space that is often empty in wider terminals. WHY: Users currently see title, timestamp, and agent name in results — but not the quantitative dimension. Adding token/cost indicators helps users quickly identify expensive or large sessions without opening the detail modal. This is especially useful for cost investigation workflows. HOW: (1) When loading search results, join with lightweight analytics summary per conversation (total tokens, cost, message count), (2) render badges in the result item right margin, (3) respect LayoutBreakpoint — only show badges on Medium+ terminals, show just token count on MediumNarrow, nothing on Narrow. Data source: daily_stats or a lightweight per-conversation summary. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (result item rendering), src/analytics/query.rs (per-conversation summary query). ACCEPTANCE: Results show token/cost/message badges on Medium+ terminals, data is accurate, no performance regression in result rendering.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:34.598828601Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.401927862Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.2.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T06:01:30.401824489Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3.3","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:5