 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","title":"Feature D: Visual Polish and Transitions via ftui visual-fx","description":"Use ftui visual-fx feature to add smooth transitions between views, loading animations for data fetching, and gradient accents. Currently view switches are instant cuts — adding brief crossfade or slide animations makes the TUI feel more responsive and polished. Loading states for analytics data fetching (which hits SQLite) should show progress indication. This is lower priority than Features A-C but contributes to the premium feel. Key files: src/ui/app.rs (view transitions in update()), src/ui/ftui_adapter.rs (ftui imports). Note: all animations must respect the DegradationLevel cascade — skip animations when frame budget is tight.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:57:09.726237980Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.1","title":"D.1: Add smooth view transition animations using ftui visual-fx","description":"WHAT: Add brief (100-200ms) crossfade or slide transitions when switching between major views (search ↔ analytics, analytics sub-view changes, modal open/close). Currently all view switches are instant hard cuts. WHY: Instant cuts feel jarring and make it hard to track where you are in the UI. Brief transitions provide continuity cues. ftui already has spring-based animation support (STAGGER_DELAY at 30ms, start_staggered_reveal() function exist in app.rs) — we need to extend this to view transitions. HOW: (1) Use ftui visual-fx animation primitives for opacity/position interpolation, (2) on view switch, set a transition_state with source view snapshot, (3) render interpolated blend for transition duration, (4) respect DegradationLevel — skip animations at EssentialOnly and below. KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (view switching in update(), STAGGER_DELAY at line 272, start_staggered_reveal at line 415), src/ui/ftui_adapter.rs. ACCEPTANCE: View transitions feel smooth, duration 100-200ms, disabled under degradation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.1","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:58.596656629Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.2","title":"D.2: Add loading/progress indicators for async data operations","description":"WHAT: Show loading indicators when: (1) opening detail modal (conversation fetch), (2) switching analytics views (data query), (3) initial index load. Use a spinner or progress bar from ftui, not a blank screen or frozen frame. WHY: Without loading indicators, the TUI appears frozen during data fetches. Analytics queries can take 50-200ms for large datasets, and conversation fetches even longer for remote sources. Users need feedback that the operation is in progress. HOW: (1) Add loading_state: Option<LoadingContext> to app state, (2) set loading on async operation start, clear on completion, (3) render a small spinner widget in the relevant area during loading, (4) ensure loading state integrates with Elm architecture (set in update, render in view). KEY FILES: src/ui/app.rs (async operation dispatch, view rendering). ACCEPTANCE: All async operations show loading indicator, indicator clears on completion, no visual artifacts.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.043619789Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.043619789Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4.2","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-3nwtd.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T05:59:59.043619789Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
